1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:03,878
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor…</i> ♪

2
00:00:03,962 --> 00:00:07,257
["Tailor" playing]

3
00:00:09,050 --> 00:00:10,552
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

4
00:00:10,635 --> 00:00:12,846
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

5
00:00:12,929 --> 00:00:16,141
♪ <i>One cut, and it's settled</i> ♪

6
00:00:16,224 --> 00:00:18,977
<i>- ♪ In the world's mess</i> ♪-
- [Cita] <i>Why are you crying?</i>

7
00:00:19,060 --> 00:00:22,188
[Cita] <i>There's nothing wrong</i>
<i>if you like someone.</i>

8
00:00:22,272 --> 00:00:22,939
Huh?

9
00:00:23,022 --> 00:00:25,525
[doctor] <i>Mr. Regalia,</i>
<i>you're going to be a grandfather.</i>

10
00:00:25,608 --> 00:00:26,234
[in English] What?

11
00:00:26,317 --> 00:00:28,194
[doctor, in English] <i>Your daughter</i>
<i>is around five months pregnant.</i>

12
00:00:28,278 --> 00:00:31,823
What kind of girl gets pregnant with a man
whose name she doesn't even know?

13
00:00:31,906 --> 00:00:34,034
[Martina] <i>It doesn't make sense.</i>
<i>What if they see each other again?</i>

14
00:00:34,659 --> 00:00:35,452
[Atoy] Elaine!

15
00:00:35,535 --> 00:00:37,203
<i>Elaine, why didn't you show up at…</i>

16
00:00:37,287 --> 00:00:38,997
[Tonet] <i>I've noticed something</i>
<i>about Gavin.</i>

17
00:00:39,080 --> 00:00:40,498
- [Karla] <i>What?</i>
- [Tonet] <i>He likes you.</i>

18
00:00:40,582 --> 00:00:41,833
- Likes?
- [Tonet] <i>Crush, that's it!</i>

19
00:00:41,916 --> 00:00:43,126
[Tonet] <i>He wants to court you!</i>

20
00:00:43,209 --> 00:00:45,587
- Shut up already!
- [Tonet] Sorry.

21
00:00:45,670 --> 00:00:47,756
[Roki] <i>Can I hear your favorite song?</i>

22
00:00:47,839 --> 00:00:48,798
[Tonet] <i>Sorry, I'll go ahead.</i>

23
00:00:48,882 --> 00:00:50,592
PREVIOUSLY

24
00:00:50,675 --> 00:00:52,719
Read the names one by one.

25
00:00:52,802 --> 00:00:54,637
[Atoy] <i>Names of missing women.</i>

26
00:00:54,721 --> 00:00:56,431
I don't want to read them anymore.

27
00:00:56,514 --> 00:01:00,101
- I'm creeped out.
- Creeped out?

28
00:01:00,602 --> 00:01:01,728
Ah, all right.

29
00:01:01,811 --> 00:01:03,188
Good luck with that then.

30
00:01:03,271 --> 00:01:04,105
Creeped out?

31
00:01:04,189 --> 00:01:05,356
Hey, you're just making excuses

32
00:01:05,440 --> 00:01:06,983
because you don't want to read, right?

33
00:01:13,281 --> 00:01:19,746
[upbeat music playing]

34
00:01:19,829 --> 00:01:21,498
[Tonet] Oh! Gavin?

35
00:01:21,581 --> 00:01:22,832
He went to the CR!

36
00:01:23,416 --> 00:01:24,793
- But maybe you're right, Tonet!
- Ah.

37
00:01:24,876 --> 00:01:26,169
Huh?

38
00:01:26,252 --> 00:01:27,587
About Gavin!

39
00:01:28,296 --> 00:01:30,590
It looks like he really has a crush on me!

40
00:01:30,673 --> 00:01:33,051
You saw earlier,
he was so jealous of Raki.

41
00:01:33,134 --> 00:01:34,636
Yiee! [laughs]

42
00:01:34,719 --> 00:01:35,595
[giggles]

43
00:01:36,846 --> 00:01:38,223
You're really crazy, huh?

44
00:01:38,306 --> 00:01:39,599
Teasing yourself like that.

45
00:01:39,682 --> 00:01:40,642
[sighs]

46
00:01:41,768 --> 00:01:45,104
But if you show him that you
are sincerely asking forgiveness,

47
00:01:45,188 --> 00:01:47,065
and you've become a good person,

48
00:01:48,066 --> 00:01:50,443
your brother won't be able to reject you.

49
00:01:51,319 --> 00:01:53,154
Ah, I'll go ahead.

50
00:01:54,239 --> 00:01:55,448
I need to leave now.

51
00:01:56,032 --> 00:01:56,950
Huh?!

52
00:01:57,450 --> 00:01:58,743
Why are you leaving me?

53
00:01:59,869 --> 00:02:01,204
I just have something to do.

54
00:02:01,287 --> 00:02:02,205
[in English] Sorry, Karla.

55
00:02:02,288 --> 00:02:04,207
[rock music playing]

56
00:02:04,290 --> 00:02:05,583
- [Karla] Tonet, wait!
- [man] Miss!

57
00:02:14,884 --> 00:02:16,302
[sauve music playing]

58
00:02:16,386 --> 00:02:17,720
[motorcycle revving]

59
00:02:17,804 --> 00:02:19,180
[sewing machine whirring]

60
00:02:20,223 --> 00:02:21,099
[snipping]

61
00:02:21,182 --> 00:02:22,142
[engine rumbles]

62
00:02:22,225 --> 00:02:23,643
[sewing machine whirring]

63
00:02:23,726 --> 00:02:26,020
[machine whirring]

64
00:02:26,896 --> 00:02:28,022
[gunshots]

65
00:02:28,106 --> 00:02:29,399
[gunshots blasting]

66
00:02:29,482 --> 00:02:30,567
[clicking]

67
00:02:30,650 --> 00:02:31,693
[clicking]

68
00:02:31,776 --> 00:02:32,694
[snipping]

69
00:02:34,320 --> 00:02:36,364
[electronic blipping]

70
00:02:39,993 --> 00:02:40,952
[music fades]

71
00:02:42,829 --> 00:02:46,291
[objects clattering]

72
00:02:46,374 --> 00:02:47,458
[door hinge squeaks]

73
00:02:47,542 --> 00:02:50,086
At last! You came home.

74
00:02:50,169 --> 00:02:54,090
Where do you see a shop assistant
leaving during work hours?

75
00:02:54,173 --> 00:02:55,174
Sorry, Miss Cita.

76
00:02:55,258 --> 00:02:57,176
I sent Karla instead.

77
00:02:57,260 --> 00:02:58,803
I won't do it again.

78
00:02:59,721 --> 00:03:01,264
Oh? Why does your face look like that?

79
00:03:01,347 --> 00:03:03,892
[pensive music playing]

80
00:03:05,101 --> 00:03:08,521
I'll follow your advice now, Miss Cita.

81
00:03:09,606 --> 00:03:11,482
I'll confess to…

82
00:03:11,566 --> 00:03:14,193
To Emerson? Really?!

83
00:03:14,277 --> 00:03:16,863
Oh, I'll pray for your plan. When?

84
00:03:16,946 --> 00:03:18,448
Ah, I was hoping now.

85
00:03:18,531 --> 00:03:19,657
Oh. Go ahead. Go.

86
00:03:19,741 --> 00:03:21,159
You have my permission. Go, go.

87
00:03:21,242 --> 00:03:23,620
- Thank you, Miss Cita.
- Yes. Be careful.

88
00:03:23,703 --> 00:03:24,662
All right.

89
00:03:28,958 --> 00:03:30,460
- I knew it!
- [shocked gasp]

90
00:03:30,543 --> 00:03:33,004
Hey! Little mushroom!
Where did you come from?!

91
00:03:33,087 --> 00:03:34,964
I heard you and Tonet!

92
00:03:35,048 --> 00:03:37,217
She's going to confess to Emerson.

93
00:03:37,300 --> 00:03:38,593
Mmm, I'll push her to do it!

94
00:03:38,676 --> 00:03:41,054
So, I won't have a rival for Atoy.

95
00:03:41,679 --> 00:03:43,723
Hey, hey! Where are you going?
Where are you going?!

96
00:03:43,806 --> 00:03:46,559
To Tonet. Maybe she needs moral support.

97
00:03:46,643 --> 00:03:48,770
Go back… Don't meddle!

98
00:03:48,853 --> 00:03:52,023
Oh my! These kids are such a headache!

99
00:03:52,523 --> 00:03:53,524
Oh!

100
00:03:54,192 --> 00:03:55,026
[sighs]

101
00:03:55,109 --> 00:03:56,194
I told you so, I told you so.

102
00:03:56,277 --> 00:03:59,239
[lively chatter]

103
00:03:59,322 --> 00:04:00,365
[laughing]

104
00:04:01,115 --> 00:04:02,367
[Emerson] I told you so!

105
00:04:02,951 --> 00:04:04,494
[in English] My Baby Tonet!

106
00:04:04,994 --> 00:04:06,079
[in English] My Baby Tonet.

107
00:04:06,579 --> 00:04:10,708
Ah! [scoffs] Ah, ah,
do you need something?

108
00:04:10,792 --> 00:04:13,169
Hey! Thanks.

109
00:04:13,253 --> 00:04:14,337
Is this for me?

110
00:04:14,420 --> 00:04:16,923
Is that a puff pastry?
Captain, do you eat this?

111
00:04:17,006 --> 00:04:18,216
Me, it's my favorite.

112
00:04:19,050 --> 00:04:20,093
Puff pastry, yes.

113
00:04:20,176 --> 00:04:22,303
I wanted to talk to…

114
00:04:23,221 --> 00:04:24,264
Emerson.

115
00:04:24,347 --> 00:04:25,598
[quirky music playing]

116
00:04:27,100 --> 00:04:29,060
[teasing]

117
00:04:29,644 --> 00:04:31,187
[Emerson scoffs]

118
00:04:31,271 --> 00:04:32,272
[Emerson, in Engilsh] Sorry, Captain.

119
00:04:32,772 --> 00:04:33,773
[smirks]

120
00:04:34,482 --> 00:04:36,067
- [in English] Sorry.
- Emerson?

121
00:04:36,150 --> 00:04:37,860
[scoffs]

122
00:04:39,320 --> 00:04:40,446
[clears throat]

123
00:04:40,530 --> 00:04:41,990
- Yes.
- Let's go then!

124
00:04:42,073 --> 00:04:43,116
Captain Paldo!

125
00:04:43,199 --> 00:04:44,284
[indistinct chatter]

126
00:04:44,367 --> 00:04:45,702
You're not "gonna win big"!

127
00:04:45,785 --> 00:04:47,787
- [music fades]
- [clears throat]

128
00:04:48,663 --> 00:04:49,497
Uh…

129
00:04:50,873 --> 00:04:52,250
Captain, what's going on?

130
00:04:53,668 --> 00:04:54,919
I can't accept it!

131
00:04:55,003 --> 00:04:56,296
What did Tonet see in Emerson?

132
00:04:56,379 --> 00:04:57,630
I'm more handsome than him!

133
00:04:57,714 --> 00:04:58,548
Hmm?

134
00:04:58,631 --> 00:05:00,341
If you're jealous, just close your eyes!

135
00:05:00,425 --> 00:05:02,677
As for me, I support Sis Tonet.

136
00:05:02,760 --> 00:05:04,512
Hey! You call her "sis" now?

137
00:05:05,305 --> 00:05:07,140
Quiet, all of you.

138
00:05:07,223 --> 00:05:08,933
Don't meddle with them.

139
00:05:09,017 --> 00:05:10,059
Stop it.

140
00:05:11,019 --> 00:05:14,355
[music concludes]

141
00:05:16,774 --> 00:05:18,651
Oh! Uh, thanks.

142
00:05:19,235 --> 00:05:21,612
You know, I knew it.

143
00:05:21,696 --> 00:05:23,823
You were the one who left the puff pastry

144
00:05:23,906 --> 00:05:26,492
and my wallet here at the shop before?

145
00:05:26,576 --> 00:05:28,119
[gentle music playing]

146
00:05:28,202 --> 00:05:30,371
I was going to confess something to you.

147
00:05:32,290 --> 00:05:33,416
Ah… [smirks]

148
00:05:33,499 --> 00:05:36,753
Actually, I've known for a long time.

149
00:05:37,336 --> 00:05:38,546
- Really?
- Mmm-hmm.

150
00:05:38,629 --> 00:05:40,381
I noticed whenever I saw you.

151
00:05:41,132 --> 00:05:42,550
So, you knew?

152
00:05:43,509 --> 00:05:44,761
You were so obvious.

153
00:05:46,054 --> 00:05:47,055
So, you're not angry?

154
00:05:48,222 --> 00:05:50,141
Well, um…

155
00:05:51,184 --> 00:05:54,020
As a "fatter of mact",
this isn't the first time…

156
00:05:54,103 --> 00:05:56,064
someone fell for my good looks.

157
00:05:56,147 --> 00:05:57,899
- Huh?
- [in English] Several of you.

158
00:05:58,775 --> 00:06:00,735
Ah, yes.

159
00:06:00,818 --> 00:06:02,945
But let me be honest with you.

160
00:06:03,654 --> 00:06:05,281
I'm sorry, young lady.

161
00:06:05,364 --> 00:06:07,700
You really are beautiful,

162
00:06:07,784 --> 00:06:11,704
but you're too young for me.

163
00:06:12,288 --> 00:06:13,164
Mmm-hmm.

164
00:06:13,748 --> 00:06:16,876
[in Visayan]
Stop talking, Big Brother Emerson.

165
00:06:16,959 --> 00:06:18,294
[unsettling music playing]

166
00:06:19,253 --> 00:06:21,089
What? What…

167
00:06:21,798 --> 00:06:22,840
What's that…

168
00:06:22,924 --> 00:06:23,800
What's that "Big Brother"?

169
00:06:24,467 --> 00:06:27,178
No one calls me "Big Brother"
here in Manila.

170
00:06:31,599 --> 00:06:33,059
Do we know each other?

171
00:06:33,601 --> 00:06:36,437
Big Brother, I'm Netchai! Your sister!

172
00:06:36,521 --> 00:06:40,608
[music intensifies]

173
00:06:41,984 --> 00:06:42,860
Netchai?

174
00:06:44,028 --> 00:06:45,655
It's Netchai. [titters]

175
00:06:45,738 --> 00:06:47,448
It's Netchai, your sister.

176
00:06:47,532 --> 00:06:49,325
[unsettling music playing]

177
00:06:49,408 --> 00:06:51,035
Ah, ah, wait, wait.

178
00:06:51,119 --> 00:06:52,328
Did I hear that right?

179
00:06:52,829 --> 00:06:53,996
You're siblings?

180
00:06:54,664 --> 00:06:55,581
Huh?

181
00:07:03,589 --> 00:07:04,590
All of you!

182
00:07:04,674 --> 00:07:06,509
- Hey, hey, hey!
- Give me that!

183
00:07:07,844 --> 00:07:10,096
Ah, Big Brother! Big Brother, Big Brother!

184
00:07:10,179 --> 00:07:11,389
It's me, Netchai!

185
00:07:11,472 --> 00:07:13,266
Stop being so nosy, okay!

186
00:07:13,349 --> 00:07:14,809
Let them talk inside!

187
00:07:14,892 --> 00:07:17,645
- Go home! Go!
- We don't know what happened.

188
00:07:17,728 --> 00:07:18,813
Go home, go home, go home!

189
00:07:18,896 --> 00:07:20,398
Big Brother, sorry-- inhales]

190
00:07:21,232 --> 00:07:24,569
Big Brother, sorry if I didn't fulfill
our promise, Big Brother.

191
00:07:24,652 --> 00:07:28,072
[pensive music playing]

192
00:07:28,781 --> 00:07:30,366
[sobs]

193
00:07:30,450 --> 00:07:34,662
[young Emerson] ♪ <i>Hele, hele</i> ♪

194
00:07:34,745 --> 00:07:38,124
♪ <i>Sleep now…</i> ♪

195
00:07:38,833 --> 00:07:45,256
♪ <i>Your mother is not here</i> ♪

196
00:07:45,923 --> 00:07:52,847
♪ <i>Your mother is not here</i> ♪

197
00:07:54,056 --> 00:08:00,396
[humming]

198
00:08:03,191 --> 00:08:08,029
[in Visayan]
Don't worry, even if Mom is not here,

199
00:08:08,654 --> 00:08:12,825
I will always be here for you.

200
00:08:13,493 --> 00:08:14,452
Hmm?

201
00:08:15,119 --> 00:08:19,999
[in Visayan] Just be patient.
After I've saved up a huge amount,

202
00:08:22,543 --> 00:08:24,295
we will go to Manila.

203
00:08:25,338 --> 00:08:28,466
I will work there, and you will study. Ha?

204
00:08:28,549 --> 00:08:33,429
[in Visayan]
Big Brother, please don't leave me, huh?

205
00:08:34,096 --> 00:08:35,473
[in Visayan] Of course not.

206
00:08:35,556 --> 00:08:38,434
No, no, no.

207
00:08:39,560 --> 00:08:41,062
Didn't we make a promise?

208
00:08:41,771 --> 00:08:44,440
Promise not to leave each other.

209
00:08:45,024 --> 00:08:45,942
Promise?

210
00:08:46,025 --> 00:08:48,236
Promise, promise.

211
00:08:49,362 --> 00:08:50,988
[gentle music playing]

212
00:08:51,072 --> 00:08:56,118
[humming]

213
00:09:07,296 --> 00:09:08,130
[Emerson] Netchai?

214
00:09:09,882 --> 00:09:11,092
Netchai!

215
00:09:11,175 --> 00:09:12,260
[door clicks open]

216
00:09:12,343 --> 00:09:13,761
Netcha--

217
00:09:16,764 --> 00:09:18,307
[in Visayan]
What are you doing here?

218
00:09:20,434 --> 00:09:23,437
[in Visayan] Since you are leaving,
I will just get the kid.

219
00:09:23,521 --> 00:09:25,481
[chuckles sarcastically] Huh?

220
00:09:26,232 --> 00:09:27,233
[in Visayan] Then what?

221
00:09:28,484 --> 00:09:31,279
You will leave her alone?

222
00:09:31,362 --> 00:09:33,698
Huh? Huh?

223
00:09:33,781 --> 00:09:36,534
[in Visayan] No, no.

224
00:09:37,660 --> 00:09:41,289
I will bring here with me in Manila.
Netchai, come here.

225
00:09:43,249 --> 00:09:47,461
Wait, let us ask the child here
who she wants to go with.

226
00:09:48,296 --> 00:09:52,633
Netchai? Who do you want to go with?
With your Big Brother or with me?

227
00:09:54,010 --> 00:09:55,011
Netchai.

228
00:09:55,678 --> 00:09:57,805
[gentle music playing]

229
00:09:58,389 --> 00:09:59,682
Sorry, Big Brother.

230
00:10:00,349 --> 00:10:03,519
[in Visayan] But I also
want to be with Mom.

231
00:10:04,478 --> 00:10:05,605
[sighs]

232
00:10:06,856 --> 00:10:10,735
[in Visayan] Netchai,
I took care of you, didn't I?

233
00:10:11,485 --> 00:10:13,404
Huh? Right?

234
00:10:15,740 --> 00:10:17,783
[in Visayan] I have been
like a mom and dad to you.

235
00:10:19,410 --> 00:10:22,038
[in Visayan] She is useless.
She didn't do anything.

236
00:10:22,705 --> 00:10:25,416
[in Visayan] Stop it, Emerson! Let's go.

237
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:28,753
- No, Netchai.
- Let's leave. Let's go

238
00:10:29,337 --> 00:10:30,338
Netchai.

239
00:10:30,421 --> 00:10:31,881
[music continues]

240
00:10:31,964 --> 00:10:32,923
Netchai!

241
00:10:36,969 --> 00:10:38,220
[sobs]

242
00:10:42,391 --> 00:10:43,434
[sobs]

243
00:10:43,517 --> 00:10:45,436
[in Visayan] I regret it, Big Brother.

244
00:10:45,519 --> 00:10:47,021
I am really sorry.

245
00:10:48,022 --> 00:10:50,316
[sobbing]

246
00:10:51,150 --> 00:10:54,487
I did everything to survive here
in Manila, Big Brother.

247
00:10:54,570 --> 00:10:55,988
[sobs]

248
00:10:56,072 --> 00:10:59,283
[in Visayan] But Mom left me.

249
00:10:59,992 --> 00:11:01,077
[music continues]

250
00:11:01,744 --> 00:11:03,496
[in Visayan] She has
her own family already.

251
00:11:03,579 --> 00:11:04,872
[music continues]

252
00:11:04,955 --> 00:11:09,377
[sobbing]

253
00:11:10,920 --> 00:11:14,548
[in Visayan] But I did everything
to find you, Big Brother.

254
00:11:14,632 --> 00:11:16,217
[music continues]

255
00:11:16,842 --> 00:11:18,803
[in Visayan] I asked
everyone, Big Brother,

256
00:11:21,222 --> 00:11:24,683
so we can find you,

257
00:11:24,767 --> 00:11:26,435
so I can find you,

258
00:11:26,936 --> 00:11:28,896
to say sorry to you.

259
00:11:30,272 --> 00:11:31,315
[music continues]

260
00:11:43,452 --> 00:11:44,453
Manang, oh.

261
00:11:44,995 --> 00:11:47,039
I drank a lot of water.

262
00:11:47,123 --> 00:11:48,541
I was shaken by those two.

263
00:11:49,458 --> 00:11:50,876
What about Tonet, huh?

264
00:11:52,378 --> 00:11:54,296
Oh, what's OA's issue now?

265
00:11:54,380 --> 00:12:00,052
Because Emerson found out Tonet
is actually his long-lost sister.

266
00:12:00,761 --> 00:12:01,846
What?!

267
00:12:01,929 --> 00:12:03,722
[suspicious music playing]

268
00:12:03,806 --> 00:12:05,724
They're siblings?!

269
00:12:05,808 --> 00:12:07,268
Oh, so who's OA now?

270
00:12:11,439 --> 00:12:13,941
Atoy, maybe you can check on Tonet.

271
00:12:14,024 --> 00:12:16,193
They said Emerson is furious.

272
00:12:16,777 --> 00:12:18,362
Mom, I don't want to meddle in that.

273
00:12:18,446 --> 00:12:20,197
It's a family matter.

274
00:12:20,281 --> 00:12:22,450
Come on! You're just going to check.

275
00:12:22,533 --> 00:12:25,786
She's your employee and my boarder.

276
00:12:25,870 --> 00:12:28,456
Maybe it's okay to show concern for her.

277
00:12:29,206 --> 00:12:30,249
Oh.

278
00:12:32,960 --> 00:12:36,213
[gentle music playing]

279
00:12:39,550 --> 00:12:41,260
What do you want to happen?

280
00:12:43,471 --> 00:12:47,433
What do you want?
You want me to pity you, is that it?

281
00:12:47,516 --> 00:12:48,726
[chuckles sarcastically]

282
00:12:49,393 --> 00:12:52,688
[pensive music playing]

283
00:12:52,771 --> 00:12:55,566
You don't know the agony
I went through here.

284
00:12:58,736 --> 00:12:59,695
[sobs]

285
00:13:01,197 --> 00:13:03,324
It's so hard being alone here.

286
00:13:03,407 --> 00:13:04,325
[sobs]

287
00:13:05,075 --> 00:13:06,952
But I had to come here because--

288
00:13:08,829 --> 00:13:10,164
To keep you alive.

289
00:13:11,332 --> 00:13:12,249
Because I love you.

290
00:13:12,333 --> 00:13:17,171
[sobbing]

291
00:13:17,254 --> 00:13:18,797
You're the reason I…

292
00:13:18,881 --> 00:13:20,883
I live!

293
00:13:21,550 --> 00:13:23,052
You're my only family!

294
00:13:23,135 --> 00:13:24,053
[sobs]

295
00:13:24,136 --> 00:13:26,013
You're the sibling I love the most.

296
00:13:26,096 --> 00:13:27,306
[sobbing]

297
00:13:28,974 --> 00:13:30,851
And then you left me. [sobs]

298
00:13:30,935 --> 00:13:33,145
And now what, huh?

299
00:13:33,229 --> 00:13:34,438
[sniffles]

300
00:13:34,522 --> 00:13:36,899
What do you want to happen now?

301
00:13:37,733 --> 00:13:38,776
For me to pity you?

302
00:13:39,818 --> 00:13:40,861
You want me to pity you?

303
00:13:40,945 --> 00:13:42,404
[sobbing]

304
00:13:42,988 --> 00:13:45,699
- Mano… Big Brother, if only I could--
- I can't do that.

305
00:13:47,284 --> 00:13:48,494
I can't.

306
00:13:50,120 --> 00:13:53,457
If only I could go back
in time, Big Brother.

307
00:13:53,541 --> 00:13:56,710
If only I could go back, I'd choose you.

308
00:13:58,796 --> 00:14:00,214
[sobbing]

309
00:14:00,297 --> 00:14:01,298
No.

310
00:14:01,882 --> 00:14:04,218
It's too late. Too late, too late.

311
00:14:04,301 --> 00:14:05,636
It's gone. It's over.

312
00:14:06,303 --> 00:14:07,137
Leave.

313
00:14:07,221 --> 00:14:08,597
- Big Brother…
- You can leave now.

314
00:14:08,681 --> 00:14:10,724
- I'll make it up to you, Big Brother.
- No.

315
00:14:11,267 --> 00:14:12,434
You can leave now.

316
00:14:12,518 --> 00:14:13,394
Big Brother…

317
00:14:13,477 --> 00:14:14,478
You can leave now.

318
00:14:15,104 --> 00:14:16,647
- Sorry, Ma…
- Netchai…

319
00:14:16,730 --> 00:14:18,107
Leave now, Netchai.

320
00:14:18,190 --> 00:14:20,150
I'm your sister, Ma…

321
00:14:20,234 --> 00:14:22,653
Netchai, leave now.

322
00:14:23,571 --> 00:14:25,406
Netchai, leave now!

323
00:14:25,948 --> 00:14:26,907
Leave now!

324
00:14:27,408 --> 00:14:28,868
[intense music playing]

325
00:14:28,951 --> 00:14:30,703
No! No!

326
00:14:30,786 --> 00:14:32,121
No, no!

327
00:14:32,204 --> 00:14:34,957
Leave! Go! Go!

328
00:14:35,040 --> 00:14:37,001
[Emerson] Leave now! Get out!

329
00:14:37,084 --> 00:14:38,961
Leave! Out!

330
00:14:39,044 --> 00:14:40,379
[Cita] Emerson!

331
00:14:40,462 --> 00:14:41,881
[music fades]

332
00:14:41,964 --> 00:14:43,382
I don't want to see your face here!

333
00:14:43,465 --> 00:14:45,217
Emerson, what's wrong? Calm down!

334
00:14:46,385 --> 00:14:48,679
You shouldn't do that to your sister!

335
00:14:48,762 --> 00:14:50,180
- What?!
- Sister?!

336
00:14:50,264 --> 00:14:52,266
You have a sister, Emerson?!

337
00:14:52,349 --> 00:14:54,268
I knew it. You're both Bisaya!

338
00:14:54,351 --> 00:14:55,978
So, what, all Bisayas are his siblings?!

339
00:14:56,061 --> 00:14:56,937
Everyone's a know-it-all!

340
00:14:57,021 --> 00:14:59,189
You, I don't want to see your face here!

341
00:14:59,273 --> 00:15:00,983
[woman] Oh, harsh! Harshness!

342
00:15:01,066 --> 00:15:03,485
That's too much! Too much! Let's drink!

343
00:15:03,569 --> 00:15:05,446
- Psst, hey!
- Are you a drunkard?

344
00:15:05,529 --> 00:15:07,406
- [indistinct chatter]
- Take it easy!

345
00:15:07,489 --> 00:15:08,782
Show her some mercy.

346
00:15:08,866 --> 00:15:09,867
[Emerson] Oh, you're here again.

347
00:15:09,950 --> 00:15:11,493
You, always acting like
the main character!

348
00:15:11,577 --> 00:15:12,244
[man] Oh!

349
00:15:12,328 --> 00:15:13,996
What do I have to do with this?

350
00:15:14,079 --> 00:15:16,040
You always act like
the main character among us!

351
00:15:16,123 --> 00:15:17,041
[man] Right!

352
00:15:17,124 --> 00:15:19,710
You're the most handsome, the best!

353
00:15:19,793 --> 00:15:21,837
You're the blessed one!
You're the son of God!

354
00:15:21,921 --> 00:15:22,922
Oh, so why me?

355
00:15:23,005 --> 00:15:25,674
You, we're just stopping you.
We're concerned about you!

356
00:15:25,758 --> 00:15:27,051
That's the thing.
This is none of your business.

357
00:15:27,134 --> 00:15:29,303
But you meddle even with sibling fights.

358
00:15:29,386 --> 00:15:30,888
Well, you're already hurting people!

359
00:15:30,971 --> 00:15:33,057
You could talk it out properly.

360
00:15:33,140 --> 00:15:34,350
Talk it out?

361
00:15:34,433 --> 00:15:36,393
You're always acting superior.
You deserve to have your face smashed!

362
00:15:36,477 --> 00:15:38,604
- [Cita] Emerson, stop!
- [Emerson] What?!

363
00:15:38,687 --> 00:15:40,689
[jeering]

364
00:15:40,773 --> 00:15:42,191
Are you sure? He's stronger than you.

365
00:15:42,274 --> 00:15:43,859
He'll beat you up. I can handle him!

366
00:15:43,943 --> 00:15:44,652
[Emerson] What?!

367
00:15:44,735 --> 00:15:46,028
- You want me to smash your face?!
- Just let him be.

368
00:15:46,111 --> 00:15:47,279
Go ahead. Go on. Bring it on!

369
00:15:47,363 --> 00:15:48,322
[Emerson] I will really bring it on!

370
00:15:48,405 --> 00:15:50,032
- [Atoy] Go ahead. Bring it on!
- You're always starting something.

371
00:15:50,532 --> 00:15:51,241
- [Atoy] I won't fight you.
- What, do you want this?!

372
00:15:51,325 --> 00:15:52,409
- [Atoy] No, just bring it on.
- [Cita] Stop it!

373
00:15:52,493 --> 00:15:54,244
- [grunts]
- [people squeal]

374
00:15:54,328 --> 00:15:56,038
[grunts]

375
00:15:56,121 --> 00:15:57,039
'Son.

376
00:15:57,122 --> 00:15:58,040
[intense music playing]

377
00:15:58,123 --> 00:15:59,917
[grunts]

378
00:16:00,626 --> 00:16:01,585
[people squeal]

379
00:16:01,669 --> 00:16:03,754
Emerson, stop.

380
00:16:03,837 --> 00:16:06,840
You know, your anger won't solve anything.

381
00:16:06,924 --> 00:16:08,884
Huh? Relax!

382
00:16:08,968 --> 00:16:10,052
- I'll join in!
- Don't!

383
00:16:10,135 --> 00:16:10,970
- No!
- Hey, hey!

384
00:16:11,053 --> 00:16:12,179
- [chanting] Emerson!
- Emerson!

385
00:16:12,262 --> 00:16:13,514
Emerson!

386
00:16:13,597 --> 00:16:14,765
I won't fight you.

387
00:16:14,848 --> 00:16:16,684
I understand you. Chill out.

388
00:16:16,767 --> 00:16:18,686
- [people cheering]
- [Emerson] Stop it, 'Son. Stop it!

389
00:16:18,769 --> 00:16:21,522
- Atoy! Atoy! Atoy!
- Emerson! Emerson!

390
00:16:21,605 --> 00:16:22,439
[groans]

391
00:16:23,857 --> 00:16:25,401
[Emerson] Hey, your safety pin!

392
00:16:25,484 --> 00:16:27,486
Relax, 'Son! Relax!

393
00:16:27,569 --> 00:16:29,029
No one wants to fight you here!

394
00:16:29,113 --> 00:16:30,864
You think you're the best?

395
00:16:30,948 --> 00:16:32,866
I can do that too! Try me! Fight me!

396
00:16:32,950 --> 00:16:34,493
I won't fight you!

397
00:16:34,576 --> 00:16:35,494
[man] Give it to him!

398
00:16:35,577 --> 00:16:36,829
[man] Go on!

399
00:16:36,912 --> 00:16:43,669
[people gasping and jeering]

400
00:16:43,752 --> 00:16:44,837
[Emerson] Hey!

401
00:16:44,920 --> 00:16:46,130
[in English] One, two, three!

402
00:16:46,213 --> 00:16:47,423
[in English] And you're out!

403
00:16:47,506 --> 00:16:48,924
[indistinct chatter]

404
00:16:49,008 --> 00:16:50,050
[in English] And the winner is…

405
00:16:50,884 --> 00:16:52,803
Atoy!

406
00:16:53,429 --> 00:16:55,264
Let me go! Let me go!

407
00:16:55,347 --> 00:16:56,515
[people jeering]

408
00:16:56,598 --> 00:16:58,350
Big Brother.

409
00:16:58,434 --> 00:16:59,393
Stop it.

410
00:16:59,476 --> 00:17:00,686
I don't want to see your face!

411
00:17:01,979 --> 00:17:03,147
Go with them!

412
00:17:03,230 --> 00:17:04,398
[pensive music playing]

413
00:17:04,481 --> 00:17:06,942
[indistinct chatter]

414
00:17:07,026 --> 00:17:08,027
[Paldo] Emerson!

415
00:17:08,652 --> 00:17:10,112
[man] Hey. Go, Captain, follow him.

416
00:17:10,195 --> 00:17:11,280
[man] Video, video, video.

417
00:17:11,363 --> 00:17:12,781
[man] Video, video! Hurry!

418
00:17:13,282 --> 00:17:18,787
[somber music playing]

419
00:17:21,373 --> 00:17:23,167
Let's leave Emerson alone for now.

420
00:17:23,250 --> 00:17:25,085
He'll calm down eventually.

421
00:17:26,170 --> 00:17:28,047
It doesn't look like it, Miss Cita.

422
00:17:28,630 --> 00:17:30,132
He's just shocked, Tonet.

423
00:17:30,215 --> 00:17:31,216
All of us are.

424
00:17:31,925 --> 00:17:34,344
And you didn't tell us you had a sibling.

425
00:17:35,095 --> 00:17:36,722
I thought we were close.

426
00:17:36,805 --> 00:17:40,059
Sorry I didn't tell anyone.

427
00:17:40,768 --> 00:17:44,772
Especially when I found out
he and Atoy were enemies.

428
00:17:44,855 --> 00:17:46,190
[pensive music playing]

429
00:17:47,024 --> 00:17:47,941
Enemies?

430
00:17:48,484 --> 00:17:50,569
Hey, let me clarify.

431
00:17:50,652 --> 00:17:52,654
I don't have enemies. He's not my enemy.

432
00:17:52,738 --> 00:17:54,573
If he has an issue with me,

433
00:17:54,656 --> 00:17:56,075
I don't have an issue with him.

434
00:17:56,158 --> 00:17:57,868
Oh, Atoy!

435
00:17:57,951 --> 00:18:01,246
It's hard to get involved
in family drama like that!

436
00:18:01,330 --> 00:18:02,748
It doesn't make you look good.

437
00:18:02,831 --> 00:18:06,668
Ah, maybe that's why you have
so much family drama, huh?

438
00:18:07,544 --> 00:18:09,046
Hey, what-- There you go again.

439
00:18:09,129 --> 00:18:10,923
You're throwing shade at each other again!

440
00:18:11,006 --> 00:18:14,051
You know, Ame has a point.

441
00:18:15,302 --> 00:18:18,514
Think about it. You already apologized.

442
00:18:18,597 --> 00:18:20,015
But he's still full of pride.

443
00:18:21,391 --> 00:18:25,187
Because if Emerson completely
cuts you off from his life,

444
00:18:25,270 --> 00:18:27,147
maybe that's a blessing in disguise.

445
00:18:27,231 --> 00:18:29,191
Right? It's better not
to have that burden.

446
00:18:29,858 --> 00:18:30,818
Look at me.

447
00:18:30,901 --> 00:18:34,154
No siblings, no enemies, no problems!

448
00:18:34,822 --> 00:18:36,740
See? Life is simple.

449
00:18:37,324 --> 00:18:40,285
[laughs]

450
00:18:40,369 --> 00:18:44,414
So, being aloof and loveless is fine?

451
00:18:46,750 --> 00:18:50,796
All right, Atoy, thanks again.

452
00:18:50,879 --> 00:18:52,047
Sorry again.

453
00:18:52,131 --> 00:18:53,715
Miss Cita, I'll go ahead.

454
00:18:53,799 --> 00:18:57,302
[gentle music playing]

455
00:19:17,948 --> 00:19:19,199
Can you believe it, bro?!

456
00:19:19,283 --> 00:19:21,952
I could've been your brother-in-law
if things turned out that way!

457
00:19:22,035 --> 00:19:24,454
If Tonet likes you too!

458
00:19:24,538 --> 00:19:27,040
- But she doesn't!
- Come on.

459
00:19:27,124 --> 00:19:30,377
Hey! But Emerson, in fairness,

460
00:19:30,460 --> 00:19:32,546
your sister is beautiful.

461
00:19:32,629 --> 00:19:34,298
It's like you really took care of her.

462
00:19:34,381 --> 00:19:35,507
[woman] Actually!

463
00:19:36,091 --> 00:19:37,509
She doesn't look like she
grew up drinking rice water.

464
00:19:37,593 --> 00:19:38,802
Of course!

465
00:19:40,220 --> 00:19:42,639
Because I raised her,
and I didn't abandon her.

466
00:19:43,891 --> 00:19:44,892
And wait…

467
00:19:45,475 --> 00:19:47,895
Why is it when you talk,
you act like I'm not here?

468
00:19:47,978 --> 00:19:49,646
I can hear everything you're saying.

469
00:19:49,730 --> 00:19:50,772
It's just them.

470
00:19:51,565 --> 00:19:52,941
I'm handsome too, you know!

471
00:19:53,525 --> 00:19:56,695
Yes! I just got stressed
because of what she did!

472
00:19:56,778 --> 00:19:57,696
Come on, bro!

473
00:19:57,779 --> 00:20:00,032
That was a long time ago.
Forgive your sister.

474
00:20:01,116 --> 00:20:02,534
Then set me up, okay?

475
00:20:03,118 --> 00:20:04,786
Bro, brother-in-law!

476
00:20:04,870 --> 00:20:06,246
If I become Tonet's boyfriend,

477
00:20:07,122 --> 00:20:11,418
I'll make you the official tailor
of Barangay Tabang Lupa!

478
00:20:11,501 --> 00:20:12,502
[Paldo] What?

479
00:20:13,837 --> 00:20:15,839
[man] Come on, let's go.
Let's go, come on.

480
00:20:15,923 --> 00:20:17,674
Yes! We still have things to talk about.

481
00:20:17,758 --> 00:20:19,384
- [overlapping chatter]
- [woman] Nestor, let's go!

482
00:20:19,468 --> 00:20:21,303
- [man] Come on, Nestor.
- [woman] Yes.

483
00:20:21,386 --> 00:20:22,471
[woman] Hey, buy us a drink, Nestor!

484
00:20:22,554 --> 00:20:24,848
[man] I'll take care
of your bottle, Sir Nestor!

485
00:20:24,932 --> 00:20:25,849
[woman] There.

486
00:20:26,767 --> 00:20:29,019
Psst. So, bro?

487
00:20:30,437 --> 00:20:31,355
C'mon!

488
00:20:31,438 --> 00:20:32,773
Stop it, Captain.

489
00:20:32,856 --> 00:20:34,233
I don't fall in love often.

490
00:20:36,235 --> 00:20:40,155
[somber music playing]

491
00:20:57,714 --> 00:20:58,882
Emerson's in here.

492
00:21:03,428 --> 00:21:05,764
[in English] Tonet, are you okay?

493
00:21:07,266 --> 00:21:08,392
No.

494
00:21:09,268 --> 00:21:10,769
[in English] Um, sorry.

495
00:21:10,852 --> 00:21:12,271
I just want to be alone.

496
00:21:13,397 --> 00:21:15,023
[somber music playing]

497
00:21:20,654 --> 00:21:22,990
[music fades]

498
00:21:23,073 --> 00:21:25,534
Around 18 to 21 years old.

499
00:21:26,868 --> 00:21:28,620
And those without family here in the city.

500
00:21:28,704 --> 00:21:31,665
If they do have family,
they don't get along,

501
00:21:31,748 --> 00:21:33,917
or maybe they only have a guardian.

502
00:21:34,001 --> 00:21:36,753
That's the similarity
among the missing women.

503
00:21:36,837 --> 00:21:39,172
I always check on that girl.

504
00:21:39,256 --> 00:21:41,967
But she never mentioned any problem to me,

505
00:21:42,050 --> 00:21:44,177
not even about her sibling.

506
00:21:44,761 --> 00:21:46,388
Father, that's how teenagers are.

507
00:21:46,471 --> 00:21:47,472
Right?

508
00:21:47,556 --> 00:21:51,393
They struggle to open up to older people,

509
00:21:51,476 --> 00:21:55,564
so they're always more comfortable
talking to peers.

510
00:21:55,647 --> 00:21:57,441
[mysterious music playing]

511
00:21:58,900 --> 00:22:00,402
Aside from her classmates,

512
00:22:01,737 --> 00:22:03,196
doesn't she talk to anyone else?

513
00:22:03,822 --> 00:22:05,365
I can't say.

514
00:22:06,033 --> 00:22:09,328
But lately, she's always on her laptop.

515
00:22:09,411 --> 00:22:11,413
Maybe a school project.

516
00:22:11,496 --> 00:22:13,040
[music intensifies]

517
00:22:13,123 --> 00:22:15,542
The women who dated on MatchTayo,

518
00:22:15,625 --> 00:22:16,626
then suddenly disappeared.

519
00:22:16,710 --> 00:22:18,545
Mandy also had a MatchTayo.

520
00:22:18,628 --> 00:22:20,005
[intense music playing]

521
00:22:21,048 --> 00:22:22,257
Do you know if…

522
00:22:23,300 --> 00:22:26,720
she used the dating app MatchTayo?

523
00:22:26,803 --> 00:22:28,555
Do you know that app?

524
00:22:30,515 --> 00:22:31,475
- I don't know…
- [Atoy] Where's her laptop?

525
00:22:31,558 --> 00:22:33,018
Where's her laptop?

526
00:22:37,439 --> 00:22:38,899
- Here.
- [Atoy] Ah.

527
00:22:39,441 --> 00:22:40,650
[soft grunt]

528
00:22:47,074 --> 00:22:49,117
- [laptop blips]
- There. Here it is.

529
00:22:50,202 --> 00:22:51,912
This is the last app she used.

530
00:22:51,995 --> 00:22:52,829
MatchTayo.

531
00:22:52,913 --> 00:22:55,457
This… This is the app used by another girl

532
00:22:55,540 --> 00:22:57,375
who's been missing for a month now.

533
00:22:57,459 --> 00:22:59,127
She met her date here.

534
00:22:59,211 --> 00:23:00,045
My God!

535
00:23:00,128 --> 00:23:01,129
[Rachel inhales]

536
00:23:01,213 --> 00:23:02,714
Do you know her username and password?

537
00:23:02,798 --> 00:23:03,632
Ah, no.

538
00:23:04,382 --> 00:23:06,301
Okay. Wait.

539
00:23:07,677 --> 00:23:09,137
[laptop key clicks]

540
00:23:09,221 --> 00:23:10,097
[laptop blips]

541
00:23:10,180 --> 00:23:11,348
[music continues]

542
00:23:11,431 --> 00:23:12,265
[Peping] You were able to open it?

543
00:23:12,849 --> 00:23:13,934
How did you do that?

544
00:23:14,017 --> 00:23:17,145
No, the site was still
in the default browser setting.

545
00:23:17,229 --> 00:23:18,939
And here, her username and password

546
00:23:19,022 --> 00:23:21,108
were still registered and logged in.

547
00:23:21,191 --> 00:23:22,818
I don't understand.

548
00:23:22,901 --> 00:23:24,861
But go ahead, son. Six seven.

549
00:23:26,029 --> 00:23:28,824
[mysterious music playing]

550
00:23:32,661 --> 00:23:33,537
[laptop key clicks]

551
00:23:33,620 --> 00:23:34,496
[laptop blips]

552
00:23:34,579 --> 00:23:35,997
There! Bingo!

553
00:23:36,081 --> 00:23:37,040
Who's Bingo?

554
00:23:37,124 --> 00:23:39,209
No, Father. It means
I opened it. I got in.

555
00:23:39,292 --> 00:23:40,293
Here, I see it now.

556
00:23:41,419 --> 00:23:43,505
Here, here. This is the last person
she talked to.

557
00:23:44,297 --> 00:23:48,009
They said they'd meet last Friday.

558
00:23:48,093 --> 00:23:50,428
Friday. That was the last day
before she disappeared.

559
00:23:50,512 --> 00:23:51,805
Where?

560
00:23:51,888 --> 00:23:52,722
It doesn't say, but here, look.

561
00:23:52,806 --> 00:23:54,391
He asked for Queenie's number.

562
00:23:54,474 --> 00:23:56,977
There. So most likely,
they were talking on the cellphone.

563
00:23:57,060 --> 00:23:58,019
[laptop blips]

564
00:23:58,520 --> 00:24:01,231
Raki. Raki Roman.

565
00:24:03,984 --> 00:24:09,823
[bustling chattering]

566
00:24:10,657 --> 00:24:12,617
[in English] Hey! I know you!

567
00:24:12,701 --> 00:24:13,785
[ominous music playing]

568
00:24:13,869 --> 00:24:15,704
- Are you alone?
- Isn't it obvious?

569
00:24:17,497 --> 00:24:18,748
What's your name again?

570
00:24:19,332 --> 00:24:20,333
Sorry, I'll just order.

571
00:24:20,417 --> 00:24:22,377
Ah, I have a table there. Come on.

572
00:24:22,460 --> 00:24:24,796
Ah, no. I'm fine here.

573
00:24:24,880 --> 00:24:26,298
[in English] Hey, I'm trying
to be nice here.

574
00:24:26,381 --> 00:24:27,424
Why are you so arrogant?

575
00:24:28,383 --> 00:24:30,302
I just want to drink alone!

576
00:24:31,052 --> 00:24:32,846
[in Visayan] One more,
and I will really hit you.

577
00:24:32,929 --> 00:24:34,347
Hey. What's that?

578
00:24:34,431 --> 00:24:36,349
If you don't translate that,

579
00:24:36,433 --> 00:24:37,392
I won't let you go!

580
00:24:37,475 --> 00:24:39,060
Maybe you're already selling me out!

581
00:24:39,144 --> 00:24:40,312
[barman] Raki!

582
00:24:40,979 --> 00:24:42,063
Leave Tonet alone.

583
00:24:44,316 --> 00:24:45,942
[bustling chattering]

584
00:24:48,570 --> 00:24:50,822
Is this Queenie's type?

585
00:24:51,531 --> 00:24:53,450
Can you find that man, Atoy?

586
00:24:53,533 --> 00:24:54,993
[tense music playing]

587
00:24:55,076 --> 00:24:55,911
Father.

588
00:24:57,329 --> 00:24:59,539
Even if he hides in the eye of a needle,

589
00:25:00,373 --> 00:25:01,416
I'll find him.

590
00:25:02,667 --> 00:25:07,005
[music intensifies]

591
00:25:07,088 --> 00:25:10,425
[electronic blipping]

592
00:25:17,599 --> 00:25:18,516
After Queenie,

593
00:25:18,600 --> 00:25:21,561
I'll focus on Ibyang,
so she can be helped too.

594
00:25:21,645 --> 00:25:24,231
You'll look for Ibyang's parents?

595
00:25:24,314 --> 00:25:26,316
[in English] Dear, I'm worried about you.

596
00:25:26,399 --> 00:25:28,735
You might get too obsessed with that man,

597
00:25:28,818 --> 00:25:31,196
when he's not even looking for you.

598
00:25:31,279 --> 00:25:34,074
[Mercado on phone]
<i>I spoke with Mr. Regalia's child.</i>

599
00:25:34,157 --> 00:25:35,575
She's looking for something.

600
00:25:35,659 --> 00:25:37,869
<i>She wants to meet you first.</i>

601
00:25:37,953 --> 00:25:40,538
Karla, why are you befriending
people like that?

602
00:25:40,622 --> 00:25:41,873
Mom, it's not like that!

603
00:25:41,957 --> 00:25:43,708
He has a punk rock band!

604
00:25:43,792 --> 00:25:44,668
Munting Sigaw!

605
00:25:44,751 --> 00:25:47,712
That's what Sis Tonet
was listening to earlier.

606
00:25:47,796 --> 00:25:49,381
[Atoy] I'm just looking for someone!

607
00:25:49,464 --> 00:25:51,049
His name is Raki Roman.

608
00:25:51,132 --> 00:25:52,217
[grunting]

609
00:25:52,300 --> 00:25:54,761
[grunting and groaning]

610
00:25:54,844 --> 00:25:56,888
[swishes]

611
00:25:56,972 --> 00:25:57,931
‪UP NEXT

612
00:25:58,014 --> 00:25:59,724
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor…</i> ♪

613
00:25:59,808 --> 00:26:01,518
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

614
00:26:01,601 --> 00:26:03,687
‪Subtitle translation by: Rachel C. Arias
